<Author>DG23
<Content>Great stopover value motel minutes from downtown Seattle Stayed there July 18th, a Friday night. The rooms were clean. The decor was spare, as you'd expect for a stopover motel. Had no problems with any noise from any neighbors. Traffic noise was muffled as soon as the doors and windows were closed. The resident hotel manager was particularly helpful. We really liked him. The parking is easy. The buses into downtown and the Space Needle run right by the motel. You have to walk over a bridge and down about 4 blocks, but they're every 15 minutes. The only thing we actually noticed not up to snuff was that the towels were a little threadbare. All and all, this is great stopover value for a motel that is so close to downtown. You can leave your car there all day and take the bus instead of paying 20/day parking downtown. 
